# Website Platform Governance

Use the documented website foundation before changing `website/`:
- `docs/platforms/website/overview.md`
- `docs/platforms/website/repository-inventory.md`
- `docs/platforms/website/component-structure.md`
- `docs/platforms/website/ui-foundation.md`
- `docs/platforms/website/data-flow-and-gql.md`
- `docs/platforms/website/graphql-mirror-and-tooling.md`
- `docs/platforms/website/shared-ui-and-shell.md`
- `docs/platforms/website/ssr-boot-and-startup.md`
- `docs/platforms/website/flow-auth.md`
- `docs/platforms/website/flow-customer-organization.md`
- `docs/platforms/website/route-registry-contract.md`
- `docs/invariants/website.md`
- `.cursor/skills/website-platform-governance/SKILL.md`
- `.cursor/rules/website-customer-organization-setup-gate.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/website-react-icons-export-guard.mdc`

Current website constraints:
- `website/` is its own git repository.
- The platform is an SSR scaffold built around `src/client/*`, `src/server/*`, and `src/resources/configs/web-core.ts` — the same `@my-ssr/web-core` scaffold family as `cpanel/`.
- Respect the current folder ownership split: `resources/`, `services/`, `ui/base/`, `ui/components/`, `ui/layouts/`, `ui/pages/`, and `types/`.
- `ui/base/` is infrastructure bound to the shared framework/tooling layer; product/business reusable UI belongs in `ui/components/`.
- Use `ui/base/components/Utils.tsx` plus `resources/configs/theme.ts` and `resources/configs/utils.ts` as the web UI foundation instead of inventing a parallel styling system.
- Brand colors: navy `#0B2057`, orange `#EC6901` from `theme.ts`. Use `SemanticColors.primary` / `SemanticColors.accent` from `theme.ts`.
- When composing through `Utils`, prefer existing component props over `baseCssStyle`/`cssStyle`; use raw style escapes only for behavior the primitive props do not already expose.
- Drawer/header-launched authed subpages (no `showBottomBar`) MUST declare route `breadcrumb` before ship — `.cursor/rules/website-authed-drawer-subpage-governance.mdc`, `docs/invariants/website.md`.
- `Loadable` inside a filled action control MUST derive `lightBackground` from the resolved tone — `.cursor/rules/website-action-control-loader-contrast.mdc`.
- Extend website-specific `@my-ssr/web-core` route metadata only through `src/types/extends/global.ts`.
- `.cursor/rules/website-route-registry-governance.mdc` + `docs/platforms/website/route-registry-contract.md` — customer router only; fixed-before-`:id` on same prefix.
- Do not place website auth-routing middleware in `web-core.router.beforePageLoading`; keep router middleware invocation in the page lifecycle layer (`src/app/ui/base/core/MyPage.tsx`).
- Locale switching is cookie + full reload only via `changeLocale(myInstance)(newLocale)`.
- Generic presentational components belong at top-level `src/app/ui/components/`.
- Prefer requester/form-boundary submission with shared action components.

Actor and backend coupling:
- **Target:** typed website actor model is **CUSTOMER + visitor** on `/website`.
- Backend integration aligns with `/website` surface: `FORMS.R` (visitor), `FORMS.CUSTOMER.R`, `DATA_ADAPTERS.GQL`, `CUSTOM.START`.
- GQL mirrors: `base` + `customer` only under `src/types/gql/**`. Supervisor mirrors are a **cpanel** concern.
- Requesters: `auth`, `customer`, `notification`, `subscription` on website platform (see `backend/requesters.website.ts`).

Web-native authoring:
- Author for SSR web using documented `cpanel/` patterns where applicable.

When making material website architecture or contract changes, update the website docs in the same task.
